      <section eId="sec_CHC-640">
        <num>CHC 640</num>
        <heading>640.  Service and return; child; resident parent; counsel</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-640__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>For a child, through counsel, and for a parent who resides within the state, service
of the petition, summons, and notice shall be made as soon as possible, and not less than
fifteen days prior to commencement of the adjudication hearing on the matter, by any of the
following means:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-640__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Personal service.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-640__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Domiciliary service.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-640__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Certified mail.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-640__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Electronic mail to the electronic mail address provided by counsel for the child
or expressly designated by the parent in a pleading, at the continued custody or continued
safety plan hearing, or at any other hearing at which the parent personally appeared before
the court.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-640__subsec_A__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Actual delivery by a commercial courier.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-640__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The person effecting service shall execute a return and, if service was made by
certified mail, the return receipt shall be attached thereto.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-640__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Service by electronic mail is complete upon transmission, provided that the sender
receives an electronic confirmation of delivery.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73233</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
